  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">F.o.b. Destination is Far clause 52.247-34 effective Jan 1991, incorporated by reference in the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795800</data>
</node>
<node id="Section G Contract Administration Data">
  <data key="d0">Section G Contract Administration Data</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section G Contract Administration Data details contract administration assignment, cor appointment, blanket task orders, performance assessment, and payment instructions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795800</data>
</node>
<node id="Contracting Officer Representative">
  <data key="d0">Contracting Officer Representative</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Contracting Officer Representative is appointed to assist in contract administration, providing instructions on limitations, deadlines, inspection, and acceptance of deliverables, with name, address, and email to be determined.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795800</data>
</node>
<node id="Blanket Task Order">
  <data key="d0">Blanket Task Order</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Blanket Task Order allows the government to issue orders with bulk funding for non-recurring work, requiring contracting officer authorization to commence performance, including a firm fixed-price not-to-exceed amount.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795800</data>
</node>
<node id="Wide Area Workflow">
  <data key="d0">Wide Area Workflow</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Wide Area Workflow is an electronic system for processing vendor payment requests and receiving reports, requiring contractor registration and use of specific document types and routing data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795800</data>
</node>
<node id="Contracting Officer">
  <data key="d0">Contracting Officer</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Contracting Officer specifies time limits for negotiating the Small Business Subcontracting Plan and handles notifications and evaluations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Contracting Officer directs work resumption after discoveries, approves substitutions, receives notifications, and holds sole authority to bind the Government.&lt;SEP&gt;The Contracting Officer deems appropriate methodologies for price evaluation consistent with FAR 15.404-1.&lt;SEP&gt;Contracting Officer oversees contract administration, appoints the cor, and authorizes work under blanket task orders.&lt;SEP&gt;Contracting Officer is the government official who coordinates the pre-performance conference, determines its timing, and administers contract scheduling and work.&lt;SEP&gt;The Contracting Officer exercises options, provides notices, evaluates offers, requires rerepresentations, and establishes unilateral rates if certifications are not submitted.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795800</data>
</node>
<node id="Historical And Archaeological Resources">
  <data key="d0">Historical And Archaeological Resources</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Historical And Archaeological Resources requirement mandates protection and immediate reporting of discovered items or human remains to the contracting officer, with work stoppage in the area until directed to resume, and government retention of ownership.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795800</data>
</node>
<node id="FedMall">
  <data key="d0">FedMall</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">FedMall is a U.S. Government-owned web-based ordering system that enables Department of Defense and Federal activities to search for and order goods and services, requiring contractor registration and catalog upload.&lt;SEP&gt;FedMall is a government-owned web-based ordering system for dod and federal activities to search and order goods and services, requiring contractor registration, catalog upload, and acceptance of gcpc orders for iq services without markup.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795800</data>
</node>
<node id="United States">
  <data key="d0">United States</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">United States is the country code and location for all specified inspection and delivery points.&lt;SEP&gt;United States is the country designated by code USA for the place of performance in option line items and contract administration.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795800</data>
</node>
<node id="N69450">
  <data key="d0">N69450</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">N69450 is the DoDAAC assigned for Issue By and Admin in the Wide Area Workflow routing data table.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795800</data>
</node>
<node id="N68732">
  <data key="d0">N68732</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">N68732 is the DoDAAC assigned for Pay Official in the Wide Area Workflow routing data table.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795800</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H Special Contract Requirements">
  <data key="d0">Section H Special Contract Requirements</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H Special Contract Requirements outlines special provisions including protection of historical and archaeological resources and requirements for FedMall usage during contract transition.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795800</data>
</node>
<node id="Contractor Performance Assessment Reporting System Cpars">
  <data key="d0">Contractor Performance Assessment Reporting System Cpars</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Contractor Performance Assessment Reporting System Cpars is the online system at http://www.cpars.gov/ used for evaluating contractor performance, requiring the contractor to provide contact information for receiving draft evaluations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795800</data>
</node>
<node id="System For Award Management Sam">
  <data key="d0">System For Award Management Sam</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">System For Award Management Sam at https://www.sam.gov is the registry where the contractor must have a designated electronic business point of contact for Wide Area Workflow access.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795800</data>
</node>
