<node id="Contracting Officer's Representative Clause">
  <data key="d0">Contracting Officer's Representative Clause</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Contracting Officer's Representative Clause is DFARS 252.201-7000 effective Dec 1991, incorporated by reference for defining the COR role.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795801</data>
</node>
<node id="Solicitation N6945025R0003">
  <data key="d0">Solicitation N6945025R0003</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Solicitation N6945025R0003 is the contract document that includes sections on inspection, acceptance, and delivery schedules.&lt;SEP&gt;Solicitation N6945025R0003 is a rated order under DPAS for base operations support services.&lt;SEP&gt;Solicitation N6945025R0003 is the identifier for the contract solicitation under which attachments and clauses are provided.&lt;SEP&gt;Solicitation N6945025R0003 is a federal procurement document spanning multiple pages, including inventories of facilities systems and Section K on representations and certifications.&lt;SEP&gt;Solicitation N6945025R0003 is the identifier for this competitive acquisition.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795801</data>
</node>
<node id="Section K">
  <data key="d0">Section K</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section K covers Representations, Certifications, and Other Statements, incorporating FAR and DFARS clauses by reference and providing full text for specific provisions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795801</data>
</node>
<node id="NAVSTA Mayport">
  <data key="d0">NAVSTA Mayport</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">NAVSTA Mayport distributes its own electricity and produces and distributes its own water, requiring safe, quality electrical and water provision.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVSTA Mayport is a location where utility services like electricity and water are produced and distributed.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVSTA Mayport is a naval station referenced in facility inventories, site maps, work orders, and equipment programs.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVSTA Mayport is a naval station with documented programs such as cross connection control, weight handling equipment, and stormwater pollution prevention plans.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795801</data>
</node>
<node id="MCSF-BI">
  <data key="d0">MCSF-BI</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">MCSF-BI is associated with multiple sub-annexes including facility management, custodial, pest control, solid waste management, grounds maintenance, and environmental requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;MCSF-BI is a location associated with specific sub-annexes like custodial, pest control, and grounds maintenance.&lt;SEP&gt;MCSF-BI is a support facility with extensive inventories for systems including cathodic protection, compressed air, lighting, and sewage holding tanks, provided in various Excel and PDF files.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795801</data>
</node>
<node id="Blount Island">
  <data key="d0">Blount Island</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Blount Island is a site referenced in base access forms, site visit itineraries, and facility inventories.&lt;SEP&gt;Blount Island is referenced in the shoreline cleanup plan and map under grounds maintenance for MCSF-BI.&lt;SEP&gt;Blount Island is the site referenced for shoreline cleanup services under ELIN X718.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795801</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR">
  <data key="d0">FAR</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR is the Federal Acquisition Regulation, with numerous clauses incorporated by reference in Section I, covering definitions, gratuities, audits, payments, and more.&lt;SEP&gt;FAR is the Federal Acquisition Regulation, with multiple clauses incorporated by reference in Section K, including provisions on telecommunications, responsibility matters, and tax representations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795801</data>
</node>
<node id="DFARS">
  <data key="d0">DFARS</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">DFARS is the Defense Federal Acquisition Regulation Supplement, with clauses incorporated by reference in Section I, addressing compensation, prohibitions, safeguarding, and subcontracting.&lt;SEP&gt;DFARS is the Defense Federal Acquisition Regulation Supplement, with clauses incorporated by reference in Section K, covering topics such as compensation of former officials, safeguarding information, and prohibitions on certain acquisitions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795801</data>
</node>
<node id="Annual Representations and Certifications">
  <data key="d0">Annual Representations and Certifications</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Annual Representations and Certifications is FAR clause 52.204-8 effective January 2025, specifying NAICS code 561210, small business size standards, and options for using System for Award Management registrations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795801</data>
</node>
<node id="NAICS 561210">
  <data key="d0">NAICS 561210</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">NAICS 561210 classifies facilities support services for the solicitation.&lt;SEP&gt;NAICS 561210 is the North American Industry Classification System code for Facilities Support Services, with a small business size standard of $47,000,000.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795801</data>
</node>
<node id="System for Award Management">
  <data key="d0">System for Award Management</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">System for Award Management is a federal database for contractor registrations, referenced in Annual Representations and Certifications for completing applicable provisions.&lt;SEP&gt;The System for Award Management is the platform where Contractors validate or update representations and certifications to reflect current small business status.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795801</data>
</node>
