<node id="Fire Protection Systems">
  <data key="d0">Fire Protection Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Fire Protection Systems maintenance and repairs are part of Facility Investment requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;Fire Protection Systems are maintained and repaired within Facility Investment specifications for relevant project demonstration.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="NIST SP 800-171">
  <data key="d0">NIST SP 800-171</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">NIST SP 800-171 outlines DoD assessment requirements noticed in the solicitation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Supplier Performance Risk System">
  <data key="d0">Supplier Performance Risk System</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">The Supplier Performance Risk System is referenced for use in evaluating supplier performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Proposal Adequacy Checklist">
  <data key="d0">Proposal Adequacy Checklist</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">The Proposal Adequacy Checklist must be used per DFARS 252.215-7009 for proposal submission.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Technical Factors">
  <data key="d0">Technical Factors</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Technical Factors consist of Factors 1 through 5, which are of equal importance and combined equal to the past performance factor.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Performance Confidence Assessment">
  <data key="d0">Performance Confidence Assessment</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">The Performance Confidence Assessment is the rating for past performance in the evaluation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Tradeoff Process">
  <data key="d0">Tradeoff Process</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Tradeoff Process is selected for this acquisition to consider award beyond lowest price or highest technical rating.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Competitive Range">
  <data key="d0">Competitive Range</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Competitive Range includes proposals for potential negotiations, limited for efficient competition if necessary.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Significant Weakness">
  <data key="d0">Significant Weakness</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A Significant Weakness impacts the rating of a proposal if it affects meeting solicitation requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Deficiency">
  <data key="d0">Deficiency</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A Deficiency in meeting requirements renders a proposal ineligible unless corrected through discussions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Section L">
  <data key="d0">Section L</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section L is titled Instructions, Conditions, &amp; Notices to Offerors or Quoters, providing guidance on proposal submission and requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;Section L contains instructions, conditions, and notices to offerors, including provisions for late submissions, modifications, and withdrawals under FAR 52.214-7 or 52.215-1.&lt;SEP&gt;Section L is implied in submittal requirements for factors, though not explicitly detailed here.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="DART Rate">
  <data key="d0">DART Rate</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">DART Rate is calculated by multiplying the number of DART incidents by 200,000 and dividing by total employee labor hours, used to assess safety performance trends over five years with defined risk levels.&lt;SEP&gt;DART Rate measures injuries or illnesses resulting in days away from work, restricted duty, or job transfer, calculated as (Number of DART Incidents x 200,000) / Total Employee Labor Hours Worked, for five calendar years.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="TCR Rate">
  <data key="d0">TCR Rate</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">TCR Rate is calculated by multiplying the number of TCR incidents by 200,000 and dividing by total employee labor hours, requiring submission of five previous calendar years' data with explanations for trends.&lt;SEP&gt;TCR Rate measures injuries or illnesses including death, days away, restricted work, medical treatment beyond first aid, or loss of consciousness, calculated as (Number of TCR Incidents x 200,000) / Total Employee Labor Hours Worked, for five calendar years.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Safety Management System">
  <data key="d0">Safety Management System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Safety Management System is a framework including management/leadership involvement, employee involvement, hazard prevention, hazard control, worksite analysis, and safety training, benchmarked against standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Technical Approach to Safety">
  <data key="d0">Technical Approach to Safety</data>
  <data key="d1">submission_instruction</data>
  <data key="d2">Technical Approach to Safety is a narrative submission limited to two single-sided pages describing SMS implementation, subcontractor selection, oversight processes, and safety compliance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="OSHA">
  <data key="d0">OSHA</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">OSHA is a source of public data reviewed by the Government for safety information.&lt;SEP&gt;OSHA is the Occupational Safety and Health Administration, whose data the Government may review as a source of safety information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Contractor Incident Reporting System">
  <data key="d0">Contractor Incident Reporting System</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Contractor Incident Reporting System is a NAVFAC system for reporting incidents, used as a source of safety information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Contractor Performance Assessment Reporting System">
  <data key="d0">Contractor Performance Assessment Reporting System</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Contractor Performance Assessment Reporting System provides evaluations to be submitted for past performance if available.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Electronic Contract Management System">
  <data key="d0">Electronic Contract Management System</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Electronic Contract Management System is a Government internal source for reviewing contractor information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Past Performance">
  <data key="d0">Past Performance</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Past Performance evaluates recency, relevancy, and quality of recent projects, including CPARS, PPQs, and other sources, to assess trends in successful completion, timeliness, quality, and cooperation.&lt;SEP&gt;Past Performance is a non-cost/price factor whose submission is based on the relevancy definition for projects demonstrating capability in similar services.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Past Performance Questionnaire">
  <data key="d0">Past Performance Questionnaire</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Past Performance Questionnaire is provided for clients to complete if CPARS is unavailable, to be submitted with proposals for each project.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Courtney Peterson">
  <data key="d0">Courtney Peterson</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Courtney Peterson is a Government point of contact for receiving PPQs via email.&lt;SEP&gt;Courtney Peterson is a contact for submitting site visit access forms via email.&lt;SEP&gt;Courtney Peterson is the Contract Specialist handling pre-award inquiries for the solicitation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Cari Fiebach">
  <data key="d0">Cari Fiebach</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Cari Fiebach is a Government point of contact for receiving PPQs via email.&lt;SEP&gt;Cari Fiebach is a contact for submitting site visit access forms via email.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Federal Awardee Performance and Integrity Information System">
  <data key="d0">Federal Awardee Performance and Integrity Information System</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Federal Awardee Performance and Integrity Information System is a database source for past performance evaluation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Electronic Subcontract Reporting System">
  <data key="d0">Electronic Subcontract Reporting System</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Electronic Subcontract Reporting System is a database used for past performance information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 15.305(a)(2)(iv)">
  <data key="d0">FAR 15.305(a)(2)(iv)</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 15.305(a)(2)(iv) governs evaluation of offerors without relevant past performance records, assigning a neutral rating.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="52.217-5 Evaluation of Options">
  <data key="d0">52.217-5 Evaluation of Options</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">52.217-5 Evaluation of Options is a FAR clause incorporated by reference effective July 1990 for contract evaluation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Very Low Risk">
  <data key="d0">Very Low Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Very Low Risk is defined for DART Rate less than 1.0 and TCR Rate less than 2.49, indicating strong safety performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Low Risk">
  <data key="d0">Low Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Low Risk is defined for DART Rate from 1.0 to 1.99 and TCR Rate from 2.5 to 3.49, reflecting acceptable safety levels.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Moderate Risk">
  <data key="d0">Moderate Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Moderate Risk is defined for DART Rate from 2.0 to 2.99 and TCR Rate from 3.5 to 4.49, requiring explanations for negative trends.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="High Risk">
  <data key="d0">High Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">High Risk is defined for DART Rate from 3.0 to 4.0 and TCR Rate from 4.5 to 5.99, potentially indicating weaknesses without explanation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795803</data>
</node>
<node id="Extremely High Risk">
  <data key="d0">Extremely High Risk</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Extremely High Risk is defined for DART Rate greater than 4.0 and TCR Rate greater than 6.0, signaling significant safety concerns.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Government">
  <data key="d0">Government</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Government issues orders, exercises options, evaluates offers, and manages contract obligations including extensions, preferences, and funding limitations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Government estimates the Contractor's overhead and profit rates, material costs, and receives compensation through liquidated damages for nonperformance or unsatisfactory performance.&lt;SEP&gt;Government is the entity evaluating proposals, reviewing safety data from various sources, and assessing past performance for contract award decisions.&lt;SEP&gt;The Government owns and controls historical and archaeological resources, operates FedMall, provides optional facilities and utilities in "as is" condition, and enforces contract performance through the Contracting Officer.&lt;SEP&gt;Government is the entity that awards the contract, exercises options, requires extensions, and oversees contractor performance and transitions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Offeror">
  <data key="d0">Offeror</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Offeror is the proposer required to submit DART and TCR rates, technical safety narratives, past performance information, and explanations for trends or missing data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Factor 1 Corporate Experience">
  <data key="d0">Factor 1 Corporate Experience</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Factor 1 Corporate Experience is a solicitation evaluation factor requiring submission of recent, relevant projects with associated CPARS or PPQs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Attachment D">
  <data key="d0">Attachment D</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Attachment D is the initial page of the Past Performance Questionnaire used to document contract and client details when full PPQs are unavailable.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Defense Contract Management Agency">
  <data key="d0">Defense Contract Management Agency</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Defense Contract Management Agency is a government agency serving as a source for past performance evaluations and information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Job-Related Mishap Death">
  <data key="d0">Job-Related Mishap Death</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Job-Related Mishap Death refers to contractor fatalities within the past five years, which may result in an unacceptable safety rating unless explained with root cause and corrective actions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Solicitation N69450-25-R-0003">
  <data key="d0">Solicitation N69450-25-R-0003</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Solicitation N69450-25-R-0003 is the referenced procurement document outlining submittal requirements, evaluation factors, and incorporated FAR clauses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Contractor">
  <data key="d0">Contractor</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Contractor performs services, completes orders, rerepresents status, certifies costs, and complies with small business and labor requirements under the contract.&lt;SEP&gt;The Contractor must register with FedMall, upload catalogs, accept GCPC orders, protect resources, perform construction work, and comply with identification and performance requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;The Contractor performs services under the contract and is subject to liquidated damages for failure to deliver supplies or perform services within specified times.&lt;SEP&gt;Contractor refers to the successful offeror responsible for mobilizing, performing work, demobilizing, submitting deliverables, and participating in conferences.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Liquidated Damages">
  <data key="d0">Liquidated Damages</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Liquidated Damages compensate the Government for administrative costs and expenses from unsatisfactory or non-performed work, assessed at 10% of defect value.&lt;SEP&gt;Liquidated damages compensate the Government for administrative costs and expenses resulting from the Contractor's nonperformed or unsatisfactory performance, calculated per calendar day of delay at 10 percent of all observed defects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H">
  <data key="d0">Section H</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H outlines special contract requirements including historical resources protection, FedMall usage, ordering procedures, and construction work standards.&lt;SEP&gt;Section H includes the special requirement on consequences of the Contractor's failure to perform required services, used for calculating liquidated damages.&lt;SEP&gt;Section H addresses measuring performance against the recurring work schedule, correcting defects, and ensuring rework is accomplished.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Consequences Of Contractor's Failure To Perform Required Services">
  <data key="d0">Consequences Of Contractor's Failure To Perform Required Services</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This clause in Section H outlines the consequences for the Contractor's failure to perform required services, referenced for liquidated damages calculation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Section I - Contract Clauses">
  <data key="d0">Section I - Contract Clauses</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section I lists FAR and DFARS clauses incorporated by reference and includes full text of specific clauses related to approvals, damages, ordering, and options.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="NAVFAC SE Contracting Officer">
  <data key="d0">NAVFAC SE Contracting Officer</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The NAVFAC SE Contracting Officer provides written approval for the contract, making it binding.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Approval Of Contract">
  <data key="d0">Approval Of Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause (52.204-1) requires written approval by the NAVFAC SE Contracting Officer for the contract to be binding.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Liquidated Damages-Supplies, Services, Or Research And Development">
  <data key="d0">Liquidated Damages-Supplies, Services, Or Research And Development</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause (52.211-11) specifies that the Contractor pays liquidated damages to the Government for delays in delivery or performance, at $ per day, and details liability upon termination.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Requirements For Certified Cost Or Pricing Data And Data Other Than Certified Cost Or Pricing Data-Modifications">
  <data key="d0">Requirements For Certified Cost Or Pricing Data And Data Other Than Certified Cost Or Pricing Data-Modifications</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause (52.215-21) with Alternates I and III requires the Contractor to submit certified cost or pricing data in specified formats for modifications, including electronic media like CD or TBD.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Order Limitations">
  <data key="d0">Order Limitations</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause (52.216-19) sets a minimum order of $2,500.00, maximum single item order of $250,000.00, and combination orders up to $1,000,000.00, with provisions for requirements contracts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Indefinite Quantity">
  <data key="d0">Indefinite Quantity</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause (52.216-22) defines the contract as indefinite-quantity with estimated quantities in the Schedule, requiring the Government to order at least the minimum and up to the maximum, with no limit on order numbers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Option To Extend Services">
  <data key="d0">Option To Extend Services</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause (52.217-8) allows the Government to extend services up to 6 months total at specified rates, adjustable for labor revisions, exercisable by written notice prior to expiration.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Option To Extend The Term Of The Contract">
  <data key="d0">Option To Extend The Term Of The Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause (52.217-9) permits the Government to extend the contract term with preliminary notice 30 days before expiration, for a total duration not exceeding 96 months.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Notice Of Price Evaluation Preference For HUBZone Small Business Concerns">
  <data key="d0">Notice Of Price Evaluation Preference For HUBZone Small Business Concerns</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause (52.219-4) provides a 10 percent evaluation preference for offers from HUBZone small business concerns that have not waived it.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Ordering">
  <data key="d0">Ordering</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This FAR clause (52.216-18) describes how the Government issues delivery or task orders via mail, fax, or electronically, subject to contract terms.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="HUBZone Small Business Concerns">
  <data key="d0">HUBZone Small Business Concerns</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">HUBZone small business concerns are a category of small businesses eligible for a 10 percent price evaluation preference in federal contract offers, unless waived.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Default-Fixed-Price Supply And Service">
  <data key="d0">Default-Fixed-Price Supply And Service</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">The Default-Fixed-Price Supply and Service clause defines conditions for delays beyond the Contractor's control and fault, referenced in liquidated damages provisions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Termination Clause">
  <data key="d0">Termination Clause</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">The Termination clause governs the Government's rights to excess costs of repurchase upon termination for default, in addition to liquidated damages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Secretary Of Labor">
  <data key="d0">Secretary Of Labor</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Secretary of Labor provides revisions to prevailing labor rates used for adjusting rates in service extensions under the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="WAWF">
  <data key="d0">WAWF</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">WAWF is a system for electronic invoicing and payment processing, with contact information provided for assistance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Historical and Archaeological Resources">
  <data key="d0">Historical and Archaeological Resources</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Historical and archaeological resources must be protected in-place and reported immediately upon discovery, with work stopped in the area until directed otherwise by the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Governmentwide Commercial Purchase Card Program">
  <data key="d0">Governmentwide Commercial Purchase Card Program</data>
  <data key="d1">program</data>
  <data key="d2">The Governmentwide Commercial Purchase Card (GCPC) Program allows authorized Government personnel to order work directly via FedMall, with contractors required to provide services at offered prices without markup.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="External Certification Authority Program">
  <data key="d0">External Certification Authority Program</data>
  <data key="d1">program</data>
  <data key="d2">The External Certification Authority (ECA) Program supports the issuance of DoD-approved certificates to contractors for secure communication and authentication to DoD Information Systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="ELIN">
  <data key="d0">ELIN</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">ELINs are Equipment Line Item Numbers used for ordering via FedMall, including items such as Temporary HVAC 100 ton chiller and Unscheduled Bus/Van Service.&lt;SEP&gt;ELIN refers to Exhibit Line Item Numbers used for pricing allocation in the price proposal spreadsheet.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.3">
  <data key="d0">Section H.3</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.3 authorizes additional methods for issuance of delivery or task orders, including orally, by facsimile, and by electronic commerce, in accordance with FAR clause 52.216-18.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.4">
  <data key="d0">Section H.4</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.4 incorporates FAR clause 52.216-19 on Order Limitations, which is not applicable to recurring work, FedMall orders, or the GCPC Program.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.5">
  <data key="d0">Section H.5</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.5 addresses construction work requirements, incorporating various FAR clauses applicable to major repair, minor construction, and demolition efforts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Construction Wage Rate Requirements">
  <data key="d0">Construction Wage Rate Requirements</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Construction Wage Rate Requirements apply to construction work performed, including clauses for secondary sites, price adjustments, and related standards.&lt;SEP&gt;Construction Wage Rate Requirements is a wage determination incorporated into the contract, formerly known as the Davis-Bacon Act, affecting pricing adjustments.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Miller Act">
  <data key="d0">Miller Act</data>
  <data key="d1">law</data>
  <data key="d2">The Miller Act requires performance and payment bonds for construction task orders, with bonds not required at proposal submission.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.6">
  <data key="d0">Section H.6</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.6 incorporates FAR clause 52.211-10 on Commencement, Prosecution, and Completion of Work, which may be applied to task orders with negotiable performance periods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.7">
  <data key="d0">Section H.7</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.7 requires contractors to furnish and display identification for employees as directed by the Contracting Officer, distinguishing them from Government personnel.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.8">
  <data key="d0">Section H.8</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.8 uses unit prices as the basis for deductions under FAR 52.246-4 for inspection of services and consequences of non-performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.9">
  <data key="d0">Section H.9</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.9 states that Government property is not included, but Government-owned facilities, equipment, and utilities may be made available in "as is" condition for contract use.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.10">
  <data key="d0">Section H.10</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.10 limits authority to bind the Government to the Contracting Officer only, prohibiting modifications by other personnel.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Key Personnel">
  <data key="d0">Key Personnel</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Key Personnel are identified in Section C, with substitutions requiring Contracting Officer approval and comparable qualifications, without price changes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.12">
  <data key="d0">Section H.12</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.12 outlines consequences for contractor failure to perform, including re-performance, payment withholding, price reductions, and liquidated damages assessments.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Watchstanding Services">
  <data key="d0">Watchstanding Services</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Watchstanding Services require qualified personnel, with penalties for unmanned posts including payment withholding and liquidated damages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H.13">
  <data key="d0">Section H.13</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H.13 provides methods for estimating costs of non-performed work using wage rates, overhead, profit, and material estimates when Schedule prices are unavailable.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Section I">
  <data key="d0">Section I</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section I incorporates various FAR clauses by reference, covering definitions, gratuities, anti-kickback procedures, and prohibitions on certain contracting activities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Department of Defense">
  <data key="d0">Department of Defense</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Department of Defense operates FedMall and establishes the ECA program for secure contractor communications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795804</data>
</node>
<node id="Defense Logistics Agency">
  <data key="d0">Defense Logistics Agency</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Defense Logistics Agency provides the FedMall website for supplier registration.&lt;SEP&gt;The Defense Logistics Agency provides the specified supplies available for the contract.&lt;SEP&gt;The Defense Logistics Agency (DLA) provides supplies such as trash liners and toilet paper for the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795805</data>
</node>
<node id="Section F">
  <data key="d0">Section F</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section F details deliveries or performance, including location, contract term, transition period, pre-performance conference, and deliverables.&lt;SEP&gt;Section F specifies notification procedures to the Contracting Officer regarding catalog uploads.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795805</data>
</node>
<node id="DD 1155">
  <data key="d0">DD 1155</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">DD 1155 is a form for issuing orders, with the Contractor required to track and report quantities monthly and year-to-date to the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795805</data>
</node>
<node id="PGP Personal Software">
  <data key="d0">PGP Personal Software</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">PGP Personal software, or a comparable solution, must be purchased, installed, and utilized by the Contractor to decrypt 128-bit encrypted order notification emails from FedMall.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795805</data>
</node>
<node id="DoD-Approved ECA Certificate">
  <data key="d0">DoD-Approved ECA Certificate</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">A DoD-approved ECA certificate must be purchased, installed, maintained, and used by the Contractor for secure communication with the DoD and authentication to DoD Information Systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795805</data>
</node>
<node id="Quality Control Program">
  <data key="d0">Quality Control Program</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">The Contractor must maintain an effective Quality Control Program throughout the contract, with failure potentially resulting in Termination for Default.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795805</data>
</node>
<node id="Defense Information Systems Agency">
  <data key="d0">Defense Information Systems Agency</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Defense Information Systems Agency provides information and resources for obtaining ECA certificates through its PKI/ECA webpage.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795805</data>
</node>
<node id="Attachment J-0200000-08">
  <data key="d0">Attachment J-0200000-08</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Attachment J-0200000-08 lists the Government-owned facilities, equipment, and utilities available to the Contractor for use in connection with the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795805</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.216-18">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.216-18</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.216-18, Ordering, authorizes issuance of delivery or task orders orally, by facsimile, or by electronic commerce methods under the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795805</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.216-19">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.216-19</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.216-19, Order Limitations, is incorporated but not applicable to recurring work, FedMall orders, or the GCPC Program.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795805</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.246-4">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.246-4</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.246-4, Inspection of Services - Fixed-Price, is used for assessing Contractor performance, deductions, and re-performance requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795805</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.211-11">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.211-11</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.211-11, Liquidated Damages - Supplies, Services, or Research and Development, allows assessment of liquidated damages for unsatisfactory or non-performed work.</data>
