  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Covered Article">
  <data key="d0">Covered Article</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Covered Article is a defined term in 52.204-29, referring to items prohibited under FASCSA orders in contract performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="FASCSA Order">
  <data key="d0">FASCSA Order</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">FASCSA Order is a defined term referring to prohibitions under the Federal Acquisition Supply Chain Security Act, applicable to covered articles and sources.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Pre-Award Inquiry Cutoff">
  <data key="d0">Pre-Award Inquiry Cutoff</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Pre-Award Inquiry Cutoff is set for 2:00 PM EDT on Thursday, 02 October 2025, for submitting questions via the GPIF.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="180 Calendar Days">
  <data key="d0">180 Calendar Days</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">180 Calendar Days is the period for which the offeror agrees to hold its offer firm from the date specified for receipt of offers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="All or None Offers">
  <data key="d0">All or None Offers</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">All or None Offers is a solicitation basis where failure to submit offers for all line items results in rejection.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Fully Loaded Pricing">
  <data key="d0">Fully Loaded Pricing</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Fully Loaded Pricing requires all pricing, including recurring and non-recurring, to include allocations, fees, overhead, G&amp;A, and profits without additional applications on options.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Phase-In and Phase-Out Costs">
  <data key="d0">Phase-In and Phase-Out Costs</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Phase-In and Phase-Out Costs must be included in pricing, with no separately priced CLIN.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Informational SLINs">
  <data key="d0">Informational SLINs</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Informational SLINs are priced SubCLINs incorporated at award with funding, representing customer allocations without contractor totals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="No Alternate Proposals">
  <data key="d0">No Alternate Proposals</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">No Alternate Proposals prohibits consideration of multiple, alternate, or alternative proposals in evaluation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Incurred Expenses">
  <data key="d0">Incurred Expenses</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Incurred Expenses states the Government is not responsible for costs associated with proposal preparation and submission.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 15.404-1">
  <data key="d0">FAR 15.404-1</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 15.404-1 provides guidelines for price analysis methodologies used by the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Unbalanced Pricing">
  <data key="d0">Unbalanced Pricing</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Unbalanced Pricing occurs when line pricing is overstated or understated, potentially representing an unacceptable risk to the government.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="ELIN Attachment">
  <data key="d0">ELIN Attachment</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The ELIN Attachment is part of Section J and is evaluated for pricing discrepancies in proposals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Section M.3">
  <data key="d0">Section M.3</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section M.3 outlines procedures for correcting pricing discrepancies through clarifications or discussions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Relevant Project">
  <data key="d0">Relevant Project</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A Relevant Project demonstrates capability in services similar in size, scope, and complexity to the RFP, with a contract value of $15,000,000.00 per year or greater, either ongoing with 12 months completed or completed within the last five years.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="BSVE">
  <data key="d0">BSVE</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">BSVE (1700000) involves operations, maintenance, and repair of Civil Engineering Support Equipment and Weight Handling Equipment, similar to RFP requirements, required for relevant project demonstration.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="General Information">
  <data key="d0">General Information</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">General Information (0100000) is an annex not considered toward the minimum technical annex requirement for relevant projects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Management and Administration">
  <data key="d0">Management and Administration</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Management and Administration (0200000) is an annex not considered toward the minimum technical annex requirement for relevant projects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Factor 1">
  <data key="d0">Factor 1</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Factor 1 evaluates Corporate Experience based on submission of two to five recent relevant projects as prime contractor.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Corporate Experience">
  <data key="d0">Corporate Experience</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Corporate Experience assesses the offeror's capability through recent relevant projects, focusing on depth, breadth, and risk of unsuccessful performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="JM-1 Corporate Experience Project Data Sheet">
  <data key="d0">JM-1 Corporate Experience Project Data Sheet</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The JM-1 Corporate Experience Project Data Sheet is a form to be completed for each submitted project, including all requested information.&lt;SEP&gt;JM-1 Corporate Experience Project Data Sheet is provided as file name JM-1_N6945025R0003_Corporate_Experience.docx.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Joint Venture">
  <data key="d0">Joint Venture</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A Joint Venture submits experience from JV entity or partners, limited to five projects, with specific demonstrations for portions performed by proposing partners.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Mentor-Protege Agreements">
  <data key="d0">Mentor-Protege Agreements</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Mentor-Protege Agreements approved by the Small Business Administration allow exceptions for JV experience submissions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Factor 2">
  <data key="d0">Factor 2</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Factor 2 evaluates Management Approach, including workforce management, quality management, scheduling, and phase-in plans, limited to 20 pages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Management Approach">
  <data key="d0">Management Approach</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Management Approach demonstrates feasible control and management of the project, interfaces between functional areas, and overall structure.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Quality Management System">
  <data key="d0">Quality Management System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Quality Management System ensures compliance with management and administration requirements, performance objectives, and standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Workforce Management">
  <data key="d0">Workforce Management</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Workforce Management plan explains hiring, retention, organization, supervision, and improvement of workforce skills and productivity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795806</data>
</node>
<node id="Scheduling">
  <data key="d0">Scheduling</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Scheduling methodology develops recurring work schedules, minimizes interference with government operations, and adjusts for workload fluctuations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795807</data>
</node>
<node id="Phase-In Plans">
  <data key="d0">Phase-In Plans</data>
  <data key="d1">submission_instruction</data>
  <data key="d2">Phase-In Plans ensure personnel, materials, and equipment are on site within 90 days, including schedules, personnel actions, and material management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795807</data>
</node>
<node id="Factor 3">
  <data key="d0">Factor 3</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Factor 3 evaluates the offeror's technical approach, including staffing levels, methodology for performance objectives, systems approach, limits of liability, supply chain management, utility services, Maximo data, transportation, UPL, and risk mitigation.&lt;SEP&gt;Factor 3 evaluates Technical Approach, including staffing levels, methodologies for annexes, and understanding of systems and limits of liability.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795807</data>
</node>
<node id="Technical Approach">
  <data key="d0">Technical Approach</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Technical Approach describes staffing, methodologies for performance objectives, and approaches to work orders, maintenance, and supply chain management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795807</data>
</node>
<node id="Attachment JL-1">
  <data key="d0">Attachment JL-1</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Attachment JL-1 is a Microsoft Excel version required for total effort including prime contractor and subcontractors for the base period, supporting Basis of Estimate for staffing.&lt;SEP&gt;Attachment JL-1 is a spreadsheet detailing staffing levels and labor hours for the base period, including rationale for Basis of Estimate.&lt;SEP&gt;Attachment JL-1 is submitted in hard copy and electronic format as part of the non-price proposal.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795807</data>
</node>
<node id="Basis of Estimate">
  <data key="d0">Basis of Estimate</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Basis of Estimate provides rationale for labor hours and costs for each specification item, using data sources like RS Means.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795807</data>
</node>
<node id="RFP">
  <data key="d0">RFP</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The RFP defines requirements for services, evaluation factors, and submission instructions for proposals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795807</data>
</node>
<node id="Small Business Administration">
  <data key="d0">Small Business Administration</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
