  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.214-7">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.214-7</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.214-7 is a provision in Section L addressing late submissions, modifications, and withdrawals for sealed bid solicitations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.215-1">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.215-1</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.215-1 provides instructions to offerors for competitive acquisition, modified for all or none basis.&lt;SEP&gt;FAR 52.215-1 is a provision in Section L addressing late submissions, modifications, and withdrawals for negotiated solicitations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.232-8">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.232-8</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.232-8 is the clause in Section I for discounts for prompt payment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.222-43">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.222-43</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.222-43 is the Fair Labor Standards and Service Contract Labor Standards--Price Adjustment Clause, governing wage adjustments in option periods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.222-32">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.222-32</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.222-32 is the Construction Wage Rate Requirements--Price Adjustment Clause, governing wage adjustments in option periods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="Minimum Guarantee">
  <data key="d0">Minimum Guarantee</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Minimum Guarantee is set at 2,500.00 Dollars U.S. per order and for the government, with CLIN 0001 obligated at award for the base period recurring work.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="Mayport, Fl">
  <data key="d0">Mayport, Fl</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Mayport, Fl is the location for inspection, acceptance, and performance of work under the contract, including Building 1966 on Bon Homme Richard Street.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="Building 1966">
  <data key="d0">Building 1966</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Building 1966 is situated on Bon Homme Richard Street in Mayport, Fl, and serves as the address for Navfac Southeast Pwd Mayport.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="Bon Homme Richard Street">
  <data key="d0">Bon Homme Richard Street</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Bon Homme Richard Street is the street address associated with Building 1966 in Mayport, Fl, for contract-related activities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="Navsta Mayport Jacksonville">
  <data key="d0">Navsta Mayport Jacksonville</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Navsta Mayport Jacksonville is one of the primary sites for work performance under the solicitation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="Dod AAC N46134">
  <data key="d0">Dod AAC N46134</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Dod AAC N46134 is the Department of Defense Activity Address Code used for the inspection and delivery points.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="Contract Term">
  <data key="d0">Contract Term</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Contract Term outlines the initial one-year performance period starting 01 January 2027, with options extending up to eight years or 96 months.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="Transition Period">
  <data key="d0">Transition Period</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Transition Period allows 90 days for mobilization post-award by 30 September 2026 and demobilization 90 days prior to contract completion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="Pre-Performance Conference">
  <data key="d0">Pre-Performance Conference</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Pre-Performance Conference is a meeting within 30 days of contract award to discuss scheduling and administration with the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="Deliverables">
  <data key="d0">Deliverables</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Deliverables are to be submitted electronically in Microsoft Office 365 compatible format via email or CD-ROM to points of contact in Section F.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="Option Line Item">
  <data key="d0">Option Line Item</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Option Line Item refers to various numbered items (e.g., 0007 to 0027) specifying inspection and acceptance locations and delivery periods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="Delivery Period">
  <data key="d0">Delivery Period</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Delivery Period defines annual schedules from 01 January of each year to 31 December, tied to specific line items and places of performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="Far 52.217-9">
  <data key="d0">Far 52.217-9</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Far 52.217-9 is the federal acquisition regulation clause incorporated for the option to extend the term of the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="Far 52.217-8">
  <data key="d0">Far 52.217-8</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Far 52.217-8 is the federal acquisition regulation clause providing authority to extend contract services up to an additional six months.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="N6945025R0003 Sectionf Pdf">
  <data key="d0">N6945025R0003 Sectionf Pdf</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">N6945025R0003 Sectionf Pdf is the attachment file containing detailed files for Section F, posted on the SAM website.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="Sam Gov">
  <data key="d0">Sam Gov</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Sam Gov is the official U.S. government website where solicitation attachments, including Section F files, are posted for access.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="Microsoft Office 365">
  <data key="d0">Microsoft Office 365</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Microsoft Office 365 is the most recent government-installed version required for compatible, unprotected file formats in deliverable submissions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="Cd-Rom">
  <data key="d0">Cd-Rom</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Cd-Rom serves as an alternative submission medium for deliverables when email attachments exceed file size limits.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="Outlying Areas">
  <data key="d0">Outlying Areas</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Outlying areas are additional sites supported by Naval Station Mayport and Marine Corps Support Facility Blount Island commands for contract performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="52.217-8 Option to Extend Services">
  <data key="d0">52.217-8 Option to Extend Services</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This clause allows the Government to require continued performance of services within contract limits and rates, adjustable only by revisions to prevailing labor rates from the Secretary of Labor, with total extension not exceeding 6 months, exercisable by written notice prior to contract expiration.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="52.217-9 Option to Extend the Term of the Contract">
  <data key="d0">52.217-9 Option to Extend the Term of the Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This clause permits the Government to extend the contract term by written notice prior to completion of the current period, with preliminary notice at least 30 days before expiration, and total duration including options not exceeding 96 months.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="52.219-4 Notice of Price Evaluation Preference for HUBZone Small Business Concerns">
  <data key="d0">52.219-4 Notice of Price Evaluation Preference for HUBZone Small Business Concerns</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This clause establishes a 10 percent price evaluation preference for offers from HUBZone small business concerns that have not waived it, applied on a line item basis before other factors, with award preference to HUBZone concerns in ties with large businesses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795808</data>
</node>
<node id="HUBZone Small Business Concern">
  <data key="d0">HUBZone Small Business Concern</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A HUBZone small business concern is eligible for price evaluation preferences unless waived, and in joint ventures must perform at least 40 percent of aggregate work beyond administrative functions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="52.219-28 Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation">
  <data key="d0">52.219-28 Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This clause requires contractors who represented as small business concerns to rerepresent size and socioeconomic status upon events like novation, merger, or for long-term contracts within specified timeframes, using SAM or specific formats.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="Small Business Concern">
  <data key="d0">Small Business Concern</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A small business concern is independently owned, operated, not dominant in its field, qualified under 13 CFR part 121 size standards, including affiliates determined by factors like ownership and management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="Long-term Contract">
  <data key="d0">Long-term Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A long-term contract exceeds five years in duration, including options, but excludes extensions up to six months under clauses like 52.217-8.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="52.222-42 Statement of Equivalent Rates for Federal Hires">
  <data key="d0">52.222-42 Statement of Equivalent Rates for Federal Hires</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This clause identifies classes of service employees expected under the contract and states equivalent wages and fringe benefits for federal hires under 5 U.S.C. 5341 or 5332, for informational purposes only.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="52.242-4 Certification of Final Indirect Costs">
  <data key="d0">52.242-4 Certification of Final Indirect Costs</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This clause requires the Contractor to certify proposals for final indirect cost rates using a specified format, signed by a vice president or chief financial officer, with failure leading to unilateral rates by the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="52.252-2 Clauses Incorporated by Reference">
  <data key="d0">52.252-2 Clauses Incorporated by Reference</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This clause incorporates one or more clauses by reference with full force and effect, providing access to full text via specified electronic addresses upon request.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="52.252-6 Authorized Deviations in Clauses">
  <data key="d0">52.252-6 Authorized Deviations in Clauses</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This clause indicates the use of FAR or DFARS clauses with authorized deviations by adding "(DEVIATION)" after the clause date or regulation name.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="252.232-7007 Limitation of Government's Obligation">
  <data key="d0">252.232-7007 Limitation of Government's Obligation</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This clause addresses incrementally funded contract line items, with specified amounts available for payment, and requires performance up to the point of total payable amount by the Government.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="Secretary of Labor">
  <data key="d0">Secretary of Labor</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Secretary of Labor provides revisions to prevailing labor rates used for adjusting service rates under contract options.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="Price Evaluation Preference">
  <data key="d0">Price Evaluation Preference</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">The price evaluation preference adds a 10 percent factor to offers except those from HUBZone small business concerns, applied on a line item basis, with waiver options and tie-breaker rules favoring HUBZone concerns.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="Novation Agreement">
  <data key="d0">Novation Agreement</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">A novation agreement transfers contract rights and obligations, triggering rerepresentation of small business status within 30 days after execution or contract modification.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="52.217-7 Options for Increased Quantity">
  <data key="d0">52.217-7 Options for Increased Quantity</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This clause specifies that orders issued during the contract's effective period must be completed by the Contractor within the specified time, with the contract governing rights and obligations as if completed during the period, but no deliveries required after the contract or final task order completion date.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="52.252-4 Alterations in Contract">
  <data key="d0">52.252-4 Alterations in Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This clause states that portions of the contract are altered as specified in the blank fields provided.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="52.219-28 Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation Alternate I">
  <data key="d0">52.219-28 Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation Alternate I</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">This alternate version substitutes paragraph (h)(1) to require the Contractor to represent small business size status for each NAICS code assigned to the contract, with an example for NAICS Code 561210.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="NAICS Code 561210">
  <data key="d0">NAICS Code 561210</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">NAICS Code 561210 corresponds to an industry classification with a small business size standard of $47,000,000 in average annual receipts, used for status rerepresentation under Alternate I.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="Defense Federal Acquisition Supplement">
  <data key="d0">Defense Federal Acquisition Supplement</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Defense Federal Acquisition Supplement (DFARS) is the regulatory supplement referenced for clauses with deviations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Defense Federal Acquisition Supplement is a regulation supplement to the FAR, with authorized deviations indicated by "(DEVIATION)" in clauses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="Service Employee Classes">
  <data key="d0">Service Employee Classes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Service Employee Classes include positions such as WG-10 Boiler Tender, WG-9 Carpenter Maintenance, WG-10 Electrician Maintenance, and others, with equivalent monetary wages and fringe benefits stated for federal hires under the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="Certificate of Final Indirect Costs">
  <data key="d0">Certificate of Final Indirect Costs</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The Certificate of Final Indirect Costs is a required signed format for certifying proposals to establish or modify final indirect cost rates, attesting to allowability under FAR cost principles.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="HUBZone Joint Venture">
  <data key="d0">HUBZone Joint Venture</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A HUBZone joint venture must have at least 40 percent of aggregate work performed by HUBZone small business parties beyond administrative functions, with representations for participating concerns.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="Clauses Incorporated by Reference">
  <data key="d0">Clauses Incorporated by Reference</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Clauses Incorporated by Reference is a FAR clause (52.252-2, Feb 1998) that incorporates clauses into the contract by reference with the same force as full text, making full text available upon request or electronically at specified addresses including https://acquisition.gov/browse/index/far, http://farsite.hill.af.mil/vmdfara.htm, and http://www.secnav.navy.mil/rda/Pages/NMCARS.aspx.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="Alterations in Contract">
  <data key="d0">Alterations in Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Alterations in Contract is a FAR clause (52.252-4, Apr 1984) that specifies alterations to portions of the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="Authorized Deviations in Clauses">
  <data key="d0">Authorized Deviations in Clauses</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Authorized Deviations in Clauses is a FAR clause (52.252-6, Nov 2020) that indicates the use of any Federal Acquisition Regulation clause or Defense Federal Acquisition Supplement clause with an authorized deviation by adding "(DEVIATION)" after the date or name of the regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759795809</data>
</node>
<node id="Limitation of Government's Obligation">
  <data key="d0">Limitation of Government's Obligation</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Limitation of Government's Obligation is a DFARS clause (252.232-7007, Apr 2014) that addresses incremental funding of contract line items, government payment limits, contractor performance obligations, notification requirements, equitable adjustments, and allotment schedules.</data>
